.SS salt.states.augeas
.SS Configuration management using Augeas
.sp
New in version 0.17.0.

.sp
This state requires the \fBaugeas\fP Python module.
.sp
\fI\%Augeas\fP can be used to manage configuration files. Currently only the \fBset\fP
command is supported via this state. The \fBaugeas\fP module also has support for get, match, remove, etc.
.sp
\fBWARNING:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
Minimal installations of Debian and Ubuntu have been seen to have packaging
bugs with python\-augeas, causing the augeas module to fail to import. If
the minion has the augeas module installed, and the state fails with a
comment saying that the state is unavailable, first restart the salt\-minion
service. If the problem persists past that, the following command can be
run from the master to determine what is causing the import to fail:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
salt minion\-id cmd.run \(aqpython \-c "from augeas import Augeas"\(aq
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
For affected Debian/Ubuntu hosts, installing \fBlibpython2.7\fP has been
known to resolve the issue.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Usage examples:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP 1. 3
Set the first entry in \fB/etc/hosts\fP to \fBlocalhost\fP:
.INDENT 3.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
hosts:
  augeas.setvalue:
    \- changes:
      \- /files/etc/hosts/1/canonical: localhost
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.IP 2. 3
Add a new host to \fB/etc/hosts\fP with the IP address \fB192.168.1.1\fP and
hostname \fBtest\fP:
.INDENT 3.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
hosts:
  augeas.setvalue:
    \- changes:
      \- /files/etc/hosts/2/ipaddr: 192.168.1.1
      \- /files/etc/hosts/2/canonical: foo.bar.com
      \- /files/etc/hosts/2/alias[1]: foosite
      \- /files/etc/hosts/2/alias[2]: foo
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
A prefix can also be set, to avoid redundancy:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
nginx\-conf:
  augeas.setvalue:
    \- prefix: /files/etc/nginx/nginx.conf
    \- changes:
      \- user: www\-data
      \- worker_processes: 2
      \- http/server_tokens: off
      \- http/keepalive_timeout: 65
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
